can hear as well.

00:01:22.220 --> 00:01:27.290
So if you have a device turned
on, a cell phone, etcetera,

00:01:27.290 --> 00:01:29.940
etcetera, please turn it off now.

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:35.250
And today it is my pleasure to
introduce a multitalented writer,

00:01:35.250 --> 00:01:39.460
critic musician, Elijah Wald.

00:01:39.460 --> 00:01:43.410
Dr. Wald, I should say, is
originally from the Boston area

00:01:43.410 --> 00:01:47.270
and he began his career
as a folk blues guitarist,

00:01:47.270 --> 00:01:52.440
and he did well traveling
the world and being abroad

00:01:52.440 --> 00:01:56.700
for roughly a decade fronting
a blues band in Seville, Spain,

00:01:56.700 --> 00:02:00.530
a swing trio in Antwerp,
and a rock band in Colombo,

00:02:00.530 --> 00:02:03.520
Sri Lanka before returning
to the United States

00:02:03.520 --> 00:02:05.830
to continue his music here.

00:02:05.830 --> 00:02:10.570
He's released two solo
albums, played on as a musician

00:02:10.570 --> 00:02:14.940
on numerous others, and still
remains active as a musician.

00:02:14.940 --> 00:02:19.480
But as I think many of us
know, Elijah has another life

00:02:19.480 --> 00:02:24.040
and he is equally well-known as
a writer, critic, and scholar,

00:02:24.040 --> 00:02:28.570
and it is in this capacity
that he is joining us today.

00:02:28.570 --> 00:02:34.420
Since the 1980's Elijah has gained
wide renowned as a writer on roots

00:02:34.420 --> 00:02:38.520 position:56%
and world music and he's written for
numerous newspapers and magazines,

00:02:38.520 --> 00:02:43.870
most notably the Boston Globe where
he published over a 1,000 articles

00:02:43.870 --> 00:02:47.110
until he left the paper in 2000.

00:02:47.110 --> 00:02:51.610
He has also authored more than
a dozen influential books,

00:02:51.610 --> 00:02:56.010
and I'll just name a couple here,
Escaping the Delta, Robert Johnson

00:02:56.010 --> 00:03:00.430
and the Invention of the Blues, How
the Beatles Destroyed Rock 'n Roll,

00:03:00.430 --> 00:03:05.390
An Alternative History of American
Popular Music, and Narcocorrido,

00:03:05.390 --> 00:03:09.990
A Journey into the Music of Guns
-- Drugs, Guns, and Guerrillas.

00:03:09.990 --> 00:03:14.590
The Mayor of MacDougal Street
is a memoir that he co-authored

00:03:14.590 --> 00:03:18.690
with Dave Van Rock, and it
served as the inspiration

00:03:18.690 --> 00:03:21.780
for the Cohen brothers
movie Inside Llewyn Davis.

00:03:21.780 --> 00:03:23.080
And I must say it's
better than the movie.

00:03:25.010 --> 00:03:26.310
